NAME

  **man** - display the documentation for a process


SYNOPSIS

    man *procname*

DESCRIPTION

    The man page outputs the documentation for a process, in the form
    of a man page like the one you're reading right now. *procname* 
    should be a single word, which is the name of the command you
    wish to see the manual for. Note that internally, man simply calls 
    dsmdbrowser on `data /man /procname.dsmd` file.


SEE ALSO

    dsmdbrowser, ps